The paper focuses on machine comprehension, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper proposes improvements to attention mechanisms, which are a key component of neural architectures used in NLP tasks. Therefore, it is likely to be categorized under cs.CL. Additionally, the paper involves deep learning techniques and neural networks, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The paper also deals with information retrieval (cs.IR) as it involves finding relevant information from a given context. Finally, the paper proposes a new attention mechanism that improves performance, which falls under the category of neural engineering (cs.NE).
